  "local_port": 42944,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "A strong moveset for **Rockruff** in **Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon** focuses on maximizing its **Rock-type** strengths while providing good coverage against a variety of opponents. Below is a recommended moveset, including move choices, held items, and strategies to make the most out of Rockruff in battles.\n\n### **Recommended Moveset for Rockruff**\n\n1. **Rock Slide**\n   - **Type:** Rock\n   - **Category:** Physical\n   - **Power:** 75\n   - **Accuracy:** 90%\n   - **Description:** A reliable Rock-type move with a chance to flinch the target. It provides strong STAB (Same Type Attack Bonus) damage and helps Rockruff deal with Flying- and Fire-type Pok\u00e9mon effectively.\n\n2. **Earthquake**\n   - **Type:** Ground\n   - **Category:** Physical\n   - **Power:** 100\n   - **Accuracy:** 100%\n   - **Description:** Excellent coverage move that hits Electric, Steel, Poison, Rock, and Fire types super effectively. Earthquake complements Rock Slide by allowing Rockruff to tackle a broader range of opponents.\n\n3. **Crunch**\n   - **Type:** Dark\n   - **Category:** Physical\n   - **Power:** 80\n   - **Accuracy:** 100%\n   - **Description:** Provides coverage against Psychic and Ghost-type Pok\u00e9mon. Additionally, Crunch has a chance to lower the target's Defense, increasing Rockruff's offensive potential.\n\n4. **Swords Dance**\n   - **Type:** Normal\n   - **Category:** Status\n   - **Effect:** Boosts Rockruff\u2019s Attack by two stages.\n   - **Description:** Enhances Rockruff\u2019s physical attack capabilities, making its Rock Slide, Earthquake, and Crunch moves hit significantly harder. This setup move can turn Rockruff into a potent sweeper.\n\n### **Alternative Moves**\n\n- **Stealth Rock**\n  - **Type:** Rock\n  - **Category:** Status\n  - **Effect:** Sets up entry hazards that damage opposing Pok\u00e9mon when they switch in.\n  - **Use If:** You prefer a defensive strategy to wear down the opponent\u2019s team over time.\n\n- **U-turn**\n  - **Type:** Bug\n  - **Category:** Physical\n  - **Power:** 70\n  - **Accuracy:** 100%\n  - **Description:** Allows Rockruff to deal damage and switch out, maintaining momentum in battles.\n\n- **Ice Fang**\n  - **Type:** Ice\n  - **Category:** Physical\n  - **Power:** 65\n  - **Accuracy:** 95%\n  - **Description:** Provides coverage against Ground, Dragon, Flying, and Grass types.\n\n### **Held Item Suggestions**\n\n- **Life Orb**\n  - **Effect:** Increases the power of Rockruff\u2019s moves by 30%, at the cost of some recoil damage each turn.\n  - **Use If:** You want to maximize offensive output.\n\n- **Choice Band**\n  - **Effect:** Greatly boosts Rockruff\u2019s Attack but locks it into the first move it uses until it switches out.\n  - **Use If:** You plan to use Rockruff as a dedicated physical attacker and can manage move locking.\n\n- **Leftovers**\n  - **Effect:** Gradually restores Rockruff\u2019s HP each turn.\n  - **Use If:** You prefer a more balanced approach with longevity in battles.\n\n### **Ability Considerations**\n\n- **Sand Rush (Hidden Ability)**\n  - **Effect:** Doubles Rockruff\u2019s Speed during a sandstorm.\n  - **Strategy:** Pair with a Sandstorm setter (like Tyranitar or Hippowdon) to take advantage of increased Speed and chip damage from the sandstorm.\n\n- **Keen Eye / Vital Spirit**\n  - **Effect:** Prevents Rockruff from having its accuracy lowered or from being put to sleep, respectively.\n  - **Use These Abilities** if not using Sand Rush, depending on what complements your team composition.\n\n### **EV and Nature Recommendations**\n\n- **Nature:** Jolly (+Speed, -Special Attack) or Adamant (+Attack, -Special Attack)\n- **EV Spread:**\n  - **Attack:** 252\n  - **Speed:** 252\n  - **HP/Defense:** 4 each\n- **Purpose:** Maximizes Rockruff\u2019s physical damage output and Speed to outspeed as many opponents as possible, allowing it to strike first and apply pressure.\n\n### **Strategy Tips**\n\n1. **Set Up Early:** Use Swords Dance to boost Rockruff\u2019s Attack before unleashing powerful physical moves for sweeping.\n2. **Momentum Management:** Incorporate U-turn to maintain momentum, allowing Rockruff to switch out after dealing damage.\n3. **Hazard Control:** If using Stealth Rock, leverage it to wear down opponents when they switch in, gradually reducing their team's health over time.\n4. **Coverage Utilization:** Switch moves based on your opponent\u2019s weaknesses to maximize damage and maintain advantageous matchups.\n\n### **Evolution Consideration**\n\nWhile Rockruff is effective on its own, evolving it into **Lycanroc (Midday Form)** at level 25 significantly enhances its stats and moveset options. If possible, consider evolving Rockruff to take advantage of Lycanroc's superior Speed and Attack, along with access to additional powerful moves and abilities.\n\n---\n\nBy utilizing this moveset, Rockruff can serve as a formidable physical attacker with excellent coverage, allowing it to handle a variety of threats in **Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon** battles. Adjust the moves and items based on your specific team needs and battle strategies for optimal performance.",
